VPC endpoints:
  Securely connect outside of a VPC using private connection.
  Elastic network interface with a private IP address
  Powered by AWS PrivateLink
  Supports 200+ AWS services.
VPC Peering:
  Privately route traffic between multiple VPCs
  Inter-region and Intra-region support
  Cross-account support.
  IP spaces cannot overlap for the peering VPCs.
  Full mesh VPC Peering:
    For 5 VPC's to connect to each other, 10 VPC Peering is needed. Formula: n(n-1)/2, n=No. of VPCs.
Hybrid Networking:
  AWS site-to-site VPN:
    On-Prem DC -> VPN connection(Public internet) -> VPC elsewhere in AWS.
    1.25 GB/s per Tunnel.
  AWS Direct connect:
    Create a fiber link from your DataCenter to your AWS resources.
    On-Prem DC -> Direct Connect location -> AWS Cloud.
    High bandwidth - 400 GB/s
Transit Gateway:
  Connect multiple routers or networks together.
  Connection to a Transit Gateway is called Attachement.


